        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 id="faq" class="text-3xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-primary/10 border border-primary/30 p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">What is automated customer onboarding software?</h3>
              <p class="text-white">Automated customer onboarding software is a platform that streamlines the process of introducing new customers to your product or service through automated workflows, personalized communications, and guided experiences that reduce time-to-value by up to 70%.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-primary/10 border border-primary/30 p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">How long does automated onboarding implementation take?</h3>
              <p class="text-white">Most automated onboarding implementations take 4-8 weeks: 2 weeks for process mapping and planning, 2-3 weeks for platform setup and integration, and 2-3 weeks for content creation and workflow design.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-primary/10 border border-primary/30 p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">What ROI can I expect from automated customer onboarding?</h3>
              <p class="text-white">Organizations typically see 250-400% ROI within 6 months through reduced churn rates, faster customer activation, decreased support costs, and improved customer lifetime value.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-primary/10 border border-primary/30 p-6 rounded-xl">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">How does automated onboarding handle complex enterprise customers?</h3>
              <p class="text-white">Enterprise onboarding combines automation for routine tasks with human touchpoints for complex requirements, using intelligent routing to escalate appropriate scenarios to customer success managers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

